  "prompt": "How do I set a default font in Gmail?",
  "response": "Setting a default font in Gmail is a straightforward process. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. **Open Gmail**: Go to your Gmail account on your web browser.\n\n2. **Access Settings**: Click on the gear icon in the top-right corner of the Gmail interface to open the settings menu. Then select \"See all settings.\"\n\n3. **Go to General Settings**: Ensure you are in the \"General\" tab.\n\n4. **Look for Default Text Style**: Scroll down until you find the \"Default text style\" section.\n\n5. **Set Your Preferences**: Here, you can choose the default font, text size, and text color. You can select the font from the dropdown menu, the size (small, normal, large, or huge), and a color from the palette.\n\n6. **Save Changes**: Scroll to the bottom of the settings page and click on \u201cSave Changes.\u201d\n\nFrom now on, your Gmail messages will use the selected default font, size, and color when composing new emails.",
